Samsung doesn't get enough credit for all the improvements they brought in Expert RAW this year üî•

Let's talk about the first one today, it's the 24mp 16-bit RAW support from Ultra-wide, main and 5x periscope lens üí•

Sure, Apple should get the credit for the idea of 24mp mode on a smartphone where a high resolution 48mp shot is taken for details and typical multiple binned 12mp shot is taken for dynamic range and color and then both of them are fused together on a 24mp surface that's kind of like best of the both worlds.

BUT, Apple was only able to achieve this in regular photo mode that too only on the main lens. There is no 24mp RAW support on an iPhone.

This is where it gets interesting for Samsung. Samsung was already experimenting with the 24mp RAW in the S24 Ultra, but the result wasn't as impressive as I would need to use it regularly. But this year, this year they went all in with the 24mp mode. Not only it supports 3 vital focal length including the 5x periscope lens, but also this 24mp mode actually retains a very detailed 16-bit 24mp RAW file.

Take this photo for example, even with all the twitter compression, you can still zoom in decent amount without seeing the photo losing quality. But wait till you hear the best part, this photo is already heavily cropped, by more than 50% of the original image (10mp resolution), check the comment for the original shot and few more crop from the original photo.

Since the launch, this Expert RAW 24mp mode has become my default choice anytime I want to shoot a RAW photo on a smartphone. It's THAT good ‚ú®Ô∏è
